For more information about the project, visit http://sourceforge/projects/vivo/.  
Documentation can be found on the sourceforge wiki at https://sourceforge.net/apps/mediawiki/vivo/index.php?title=Documentation

Execution Scripts
Several example scripts are provided in the scripts folder.

Java Library Demo
A demo of using the tools as a java library is included in the examples folder also

2. Harvesting data from a CSV file or relational database

a) CSV file example:

To try out the example, do the following:

- Edit config/models/vivo.xml and set it to point to your vivo database

sdb mode:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Model>
	<Param name="type">sdb</Param>
	<Param name="dbLayout">layout2</Param>
	<Param name="dbType">MySQL</Param>
	<Param name="dbUrl">jdbc:mysql://127.0.0.1:3306/vitrodb</Param>
	<Param name="modelName">http://vitro.mannlib.cornell.edu/default/vitro-kb-2</Param>
	<Param name="dbUser">USERNAME</Param>
	<Param name="dbPass">PASSWORD</Param>
	<Param name="namespace">NAMESPACE</Param>
</Model>

rdb mode:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Model>
	<Param name="type">rdb</Param>
	<Param name="dbClass">com.mysql.jdbc.Driver</Param>
	<Param name="dbType">MySQL</Param>
	<Param name="dbUrl">jdbc:mysql://127.0.0.1:3306/vitrodb</Param>
	<Param name="modelName">http://vitro.mannlib.cornell.edu/default/vitro-kb-2</Param>
	<Param name="dbUser">USERNAME</Param>
	<Param name="dbPass">PASSWORD</Param>
	<Param name="namespace">NAMESPACE</Param>
</Model>

- Run scripts/run-csv.sh

Files associated with this example are config/datamaps/example.csv-map.xml and files/person.csv
Edit the associated files and run-csv.sh for customization.

b) Relational database example:

To try out the example, do the following:

- Edit config/models/vivo.xml and set it to point to your vivo database (see above)
- Edit config/datamaps/example-d2rmap.xml to point to your database source and modify the query
- Run scripts/run-rdbms.sh

